{"body":"<a href="#"><img alt="P2" src="https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p2.svg?v=7" align="top"></a> **`usize::MAX` as rendering width is fragile**

Passing `usize::MAX` as the `width` argument relies on undocumented overflow-safe arithmetic inside `html2text`. For pages with HTML tables, the library distributes the available width across columns — if any intermediate expression performs a checked subtraction or a multiplication before dividing, the result can wrap on 32-bit targets or trip a debug-mode overflow check.

The html2text 0.16 builder API exposes a cleaner, documented path for "no wrapping":

```suggestion
    match html2text::config::plain().string_from_read(html.as_bytes(), 1_000_000) {
```

