{"body":"<a href="#"><img alt="P1" src="https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p1.svg?v=7" align="top"></a> **Parse errors silently return empty string**

`Err(_) => String::new()` swallows the parse error completely and returns an empty string indistinguishable from a truly empty page. Per the project logging guide, unexpected-but-recoverable conditions should use `tracing::warn!`. Callers (and operators) have no signal that content extraction failed.

```suggestion
        Err(e) => {
            tracing::warn!("html2text parse error: {e}");
            String::new()
        },
```

This is especially important here because a parse failure means the entire page content is silently discarded — the LLM will see an empty result and may hallucinate or incorrectly claim the page has no content.","line":"@@ -234,111 +234,20 @@ fn extract_content(
