{"body":"<a href="#"><img alt="P1" src="https://greptile-static-assets.s3.amazonaws.com/badges/p1.svg?v=7" align="top"></a> **`html2text` may inject link footnotes and formatting marks into plain-text output**

`html2text::from_read` (using the default `TrivialDecorator`) renders `<a href="...">text</a>` elements as `[text][1]` with a footer block like `[1] https://...` appended after the body. For a `web_fetch` result being fed to an LLM, this injects potentially many URL lines that were not present in the original text and that the old hand-rolled parser deliberately discarded.

You can verify this with a quick test:
```rust
let html = r#"<p>Visit <a href="https://example.com">our site</a> today.</p>"#;
let text = html_to_text(html);
// Does `text` contain "https://example.com"?  Under some html2text versions, yes.
```

If link URLs should be dropped (matching the old behaviour), use the `TrivialDecorator` explicitly or the `config::plain()` builder with link-rendering disabled. Please add a test asserting that anchor `href` values do **not** appear in the output, so this contract is enforced going forward.","line":"@@ -234,111 +234,20 @@ fn extract_content(
